First Lady Melania Trump visited Microsoft Corporation Headquarters in Seattle, Washington to promote her Be Best agenda. She was greeted by CEO Satya Nadella and had discussions with key leaders including President Brad Smith and CFO Amy Hood. The visit included showcases of Microsoft's efforts in online safety, such as parental controls on XBOX gaming systems, accessibility features for users with limited mobility, and initiatives to improve child safety in the digital age. Melania Trump expressed her admiration for Microsoft's dedication to protecting children online and promoting digital civility.